I'll start by exploring the repository structure and understanding the issue.

## Phase 1: READING - Understanding the Problem

The issue is about formatting single-line comments inside an empty `enum` declaration. When an enum has only a comment (no members), the formatter incorrectly puts the closing brace on the same line as the comment:

**Input:**
```tsx
enum Baz {
  // Enum comment
}
```

**Current (broken) output:**
```tsx
enum Baz {// Enum comment}
```

**Expected (Prettier-compatible) output:**
```tsx
enum Baz {
  // Enum comment
}
```

The key observation is that this bug only affects `enum` declarations — `type` and `interface` with similar empty-body comments are handled correctly.

